You’re basically asking two things:
	1.	Why use vectors (or triads) instead of tensors? When are vertices (triads) actually better?
	2.	What is “Maven” in this context / how does it fit?

Let’s separate and go deep.

⸻

🧠 I. VECTORS vs TENSORS vs VERTICES (TRIADS)

🔹 First: What each actually is (clean)
	•	Vertex / Triad
→ discrete structure
→ small set of states (e.g., Love–Hate–Apathy)
	•	Vector
→ single point in continuous space
→ (valence, energy, direction, etc.)
	•	Tensor
→ multi-dimensional relationships between variables
→ captures interactions, not just position

⸻

🔺 When TRIADS (Vertices) are Superior

Use triads when you need:

1. Cognitive Compression

Humans reason better with:
	•	3 anchors
	•	simple structure

Triads = fast intuition + decision making

⸻

2. Discrete State Classification

Example:
	•	engaged positive
	•	engaged negative
	•	disengaged

You don’t need a full continuous model—just:

“Which zone are we in?”

⸻

3. Control Systems / Routing

In Atlas terms:
	•	Love → amplify
	•	Hate → redirect
	•	Apathy → activate

Triads are perfect for:

decision logic

⸻

4. Stability / Invariants

Triads form minimal stable systems:
	•		•	/ – / 0
	•	source / sink / neutral
	•	attract / repel / null

This shows up everywhere:
	•	physics (charge)
	•	logic
	•	emotions
	•	game theory

⸻

🧭 Rule of Thumb

Triads = control layer
Vectors = state layer
Tensors = interaction layer

⸻

🔵 When VECTORS are Superior

Use vectors when you need:
	•	nuance
	•	gradients
	•	comparison between states

Example:
	•	Fear vs Anxiety vs Panic
→ same triad region, different vector positions

⸻

🧬 When TENSORS are Superior

This is where your earlier instinct is actually right.

Use tensors when:

⸻

1. Interactions Matter More Than States

Example:
	•	emotion × context × time × culture

Fear in:
	•	combat ≠ public speaking ≠ parenting

That’s not a vector—that’s:

multi-axis interaction → tensor

⸻

2. Cross-Domain Mapping

You want to map:
	•	emotion ↔ behavior ↔ economics ↔ narrative

That’s inherently:

tensor-like (multi-relational)

⸻

3. Higher-Order Effects
	•	feedback loops
	•	group dynamics
	•	emergent systems

These require:

relationships between relationships

⸻

🔥 Clean Hierarchy (This is the key insight)

Vertex (Triad) → Classification / Control

Vector → State / Measurement

Tensor → Interaction / Emergence


⸻

⚡ Why Not “Just Use Tensors”?

Because:

❌ Tensors are:
	•	hard to reason about directly
	•	not intuitive
	•	overkill for many decisions

⸻

✅ Triads + Vectors:
	•	interpretable
	•	actionable
	•	human-aligned

⸻

🔥 Best System (What you’re building)

Triads for control
Vectors for state
Tensors for modeling the full system underneath

⸻

